			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well...here we are.  I am still looking for anyone who can answer a question for me. Maybe someone on this board can help.  When I reviewed the styles of fight for a Nightshade....I was given two choices for weapons.  Pierecing or Blades.  I chose piercing (more roguish and I play on a Roleplay server).  I saw that later on down the line....that some of my moves required a "block" for an open.   Hmmm....wonder what a "block" is.  Must be same thing as an "Evade" or they wouldn't have put it in there like that.  Well...time has passed...my seasons have grown..and I have learned much.  Now...I am at the stage where I realize  "Hey...a block means must use a shield".  But who the heck uses a shield and plays a class the dual-wields?  MAYBE..there are some of these people out there.  I dunno and if there is....good on them.  PLay your character how you feel happiest.  I...choose not to use a shield as it reduces the damage I put out.  Significantly...reduces...the damage I put out.  Not just a little bit but almost halves it.  So shield use is outta the question for me.  Just not very roleplay like for a Rogue to sneak around...carrying a bright shiny shield in his hands.  /shrug
<br />

<br />

<br />
   Anyway....I have proposed this question to the Mythic people and have gotten no response...so I will post it again.  By making Tarantula require a BLOCK open....you effectively remove four or five moves down the line for us.  You know how it is....this move does this...but requires a Tarantula open.  I ask...is it not an option to make Tarantula (or any move now that requires a BLOCK to open in the piercing/slashing line) openable with either a block or an evade?  Would the coding be impossible to implement?  Reason I ask is simple.  I am looking at my skills.  I keep piercing at level..with Stealth close behind.  Then comes Critical Strike and then Envenom.  I gear towards RvR more then RvE.  I forsee in the near future...putting points in piercing...just to get moves that I cannot ever use.  Seems like a waste when you look at the fact that Nightshades are without a doubt one of the few classes that NEED 2xlevel points to keep up with basic skills.  Why make me waste them in piercing to get nothing back.   This is not a flame..or a negative post (sorry if it looks it) just a post that I am looking for answers too from one of the people in charge of something besides a coffee pot.
<br />

<br />
Please let me know...sooner I do the sooner I can decide what to do with the points I have stockpiled waiting for a home.  Thanks  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" />   <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
