			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not to flame or anything, but has it occured to you that piercing weapons may be used by classes other than nightshades?  I agree that nightshades are a bit more limited in base weapon styles than other rogues, but this is true of many weapon specs in Hibernia.  
<br />

<br />
All one-handed weapons have styles that work off blocks.  In the same way, weapons have styles that require evade as an opening and are unusable by some classes.
<br />

<br />
You make it sound as if this is a bug, or a nerf.  Quite simply, it is not.  It is the way the game is designed.  There are styles I cannot use with my infiltrator for the same reason.  Those styles are inteded for defensive oriented classes using shields.  I understand that, and have no problem with that.
<br />

<br />
The thing to remember, is that base weapon types are used by many classes, and the styles will not all be appropriate for your class.  As a nightshade, you have more possiblities than many classes because you also have the full selection of critical strike styles to choose from.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
