			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yes...I agree Revarien.  I know and understand that I am not the only one using Piercing.  And believe me I am not trying to make the piercing line appear to be Rogue only.  I am simply looking for some give here.  If it were a Crushing move that this was about I would say "well....I could have chose Piercing".  Same thing with Advanced weapons or anything else.  But given two choise for weapons...I chose the one that we all know rogues are geared to...knives.  All I am asking is that the line be adjusted somewhat.  Or maybe...for that matter...all lines.  Rangers in HIbernia are a good example.  I have seen many of them carrying shields...and many using dual-wield.  Would it not be feasable for Mythic to enable them to use a line of moves either way?  
<br />

<br />
   I like my class.  I like playing them.  Am I the most powerful class in the realm?  Nope.  Can I be?  Given the right situaitions....yeah...I can smack it down with the best of them.  GOd help the Albion healer who falls asleep.....I'll have 2 poison covered blades in his back faster then he can type /release.  All I guess I want is the chance to realistically use the piercing line and ALL its moves...without having to don a shield.  If this cannot be modified...then maybe its time to start over.  I hope not.  
<br />

<br />
  P.S.  Have yet to see a class who gets piercing who does not have evade ability.  If there is one out there...let me know.  Thanks.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
